decision_conditions: The development permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.

Reason: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended). | The development hereby approved shall be carried out in accordance with the following approved drawings and documents: PL10-100 (Location Plan), PL10-101 (Block Plan and Existing Site Plan), PL10-102 (Proposed Site Plan), PL10-103 (Existing Site Plan), PL10-104 (Existing Site Plan 2), PL10-105 (Proposed Site Plan), PL10-106 (Proposed Site Plan 2), PL10-100 (Design and Access Statement prepared by Zebra Architects dated November 2021), Datasheet for product TSM-DE09.08 (Vertex S Backsheet Monocrystalline Module) and Datasheet for product CAHV-P500YB-HPB (Heating Ecodan Air Source Heat Pump).

Reason: For the avoidance of doubt and in the interests of proper planning. | All materials to be used for the development shall be in accordance with the materials stated on the submitted application form or the drawings and documents listed in Condition (2).

Reason: To ensure that the materials harmonise with the surroundings, in accordance with policies 1.1 & 1.2 of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), policies 7.4 & 7B of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013), policies D3 and D4 of the London Plan (2021) and the National Planning Policy Framework (2021). | Prior to the commencement of the development, details of the external rating noise level emitted from plant/ machinery/ equipment/ducting/air in- and outlets/mechanical installations, together with mitigation measures as appropriate shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority in writing. The mitigation measures shall ensure that the external rating noise level LAeq emitted will be lower than the lowest existing background sound level LA90 by 10dBA at the most noise sensitive receiver locations at the development site and at surrounding premises. The assessment shall be made in accordance with BS4142:2014 +A1 2019, with all plant/equipment operating together at maximum capacity. Where required, a post installation sound assessment shall be submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval in writing. The assessment shall be carried out to confirm compliance with the noise criteria and shall include additional steps to mitigate noise as necessary. Approved details shall be implemented prior to first use of plant/ machinery/ equipment and thereafter be permanently retained.

Reason:  To ensure that the amenity of occupiers of the development site/ surrounding premises is not adversely affected by noise from mechanical installations/ equipment, in accordance with policy 1.1(j) of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013), policy D14 of the London Plan (2021) and the National Planning Policy Framework (2021). | Prior to the use, machinery, plant or equipment/ extraction/ ventilation system and ducting at the development shall be mounted with proprietary anti-vibration isolators and fan motors shall be vibration isolated from the casing and adequately silenced and maintained as such.

Reason:  To ensure that the amenity of occupiers of the development site/ surrounding premises is not adversely affected by noise from mechanical installations/ equipment, in accordance with policy 1.1(j) of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013), policy D14 of the London Plan (2021) and the National Planning Policy Framework (2021).
